creator: shippo@mail.bg
text:
I installed Apache 2.2.6 but when I try to start it I get the following 
message:
   
   (OS 10048)Only one usage of each socket address (protocol/network 
address/port) is normally permitted. :make_sock: could not bind to address 
0.0.0.0:80 no listening sockets available, shutting down
   Unable to open logs

Please help!

creator: nick@webthing.com
text:
Please use a user support forum for help.  This probably means you already have
something running on port 80: another webserver, or a parasite program.
